 about fears of invasion and pacifism, through the modernist novels of the 1920s to its dominance in the War Books Boom of 1928–30. This book will appeal to scholars and students of English literature, social and cultural history, and gender studies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aSocial history in literature. 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aHISTORY / Military / World War I.2bisacsh  aCultural history.  aDegeneration.  aDisenchantment.  aDisillusionment.  aFirst World War.  aLiterary history.  aModernism.  aWar literature.  aeDclinism.1 aFrayn, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2014 eBook-Packagez978311128357940uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152610317840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526103178423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526103178/original  a978-3-11-128357-9  Manchester University Press 2014 eBook-Packageb2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles